<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="44" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 835.73/71</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-29T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s September 28, 1916, and your despatch No. 324, February 9,
                            1917. The Central &amp; South American Telegraph Co. made a formal
                            application to the Argentine Government for a landing site for their
                            cables from Brazil to the Argentine on March 8, 1917. No reply has been
                            yet received by the company. You may request the Argentine Government to
                            reply at its early convenience in order that a landing place for the
                            cables on the coast of Argentina may be fixed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>